SIMPLE: exanimate
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Exanimate
<hw>Ex*an"i*mate</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>exanimatus</ets>, p. p. of <ets>exanimare</ets> to deprive of life
or spirit; <ets>ex</ets> out + <ets>anima</ets> air, breath, life,
spirit.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Lifeless; dead.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>
⟦ldquo⟧Carcasses <xex>exanimate</xex>.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Spenser.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Destitute of animation; spiritless;
disheartened.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark> ⟦ldquo⟧Pale . . . wretch,
<xex>exanimate</xex> by love.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Thomson.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Exanimate</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Exanimate
<hw>Ex*an"i*mate</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To deprive of
animation or of life.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Exanimation</ent>⟦br⟧
